AB  - This study investigates the relationship between interest rate skewness and stock market returns. Using survey forecasts from the Survey of Professional Forecasters, we measure the cross-sectional skewness (SKEW) of forecasters’ interest rate expectations. SKEW captures the asymmetry in forecasters’ expectations, and a positive SKEW signals upside risk to interest rates and vice versa. Furthermore, SKEW positively predicts in- and out-of-sample US stock market returns. SKEW’s predictive power is not subsumed by existing interest rate skewness measures, macroeconomic skewness/uncertainty indicators, macroeconomic and interest rate variables, or investor sentiment indices. Moreover, SKEW’s predictive power is consistent with a risk-based explanation.
