AB  - In heterogeneous agent models, systematic excess demand for risky assets, generated by sentiment, can lead to a sentiment risk premium for sophisticated arbitrageurs. Utilizing media-based sentiment on economic growth, inflation, unemployment, and sociopolitical conditions, we create a macro sentiment index (MSI) and show that hedge funds with negative exposure to MSI generate significantly higher abnormal returns. The predictive power of MSI betas remains after controlling for fund characteristics and other risk and uncertainty factors. We show that a tradable version of MSI meets the necessary criteria to be considered a state variable in the ICAPM for actively managed fund portfolios.
